name: Citizen Men's AT8020-54L 'Blue Angels' Stainless Steel Eco-Drive Dress Watch
description: Detailed item info Product Information Tell time with ease and style while wearing the Citizen Blue Angels World Chronograph A-T AT8020-54L wristwatch for men. Featuring an Eco-Drive with Japanese quartz, these watches boast the Citizen reputation for consistency and quality. Busy professionals and travelers easily keep track of the hour worldwide, thanks to its automatic timekeeping of 26 international cities. An attractive stainless steel band and sapphire-colored dial make this piece an accessory anyone can take pride in wearing. It is quite durable and offers water resistance up to 666 feet. Three chronographs are among its many other features. Reading the time in low light is easy with this Citizen watch's luminous hour, minute, and second hands as well as the discernible hour marks. The blue dial and non-reflective crystal on the watch set off the silver-tone case and adjustable stainless steel band. In the style of a bracelet with a folding clasp, the band features blue ion plating. The strap width is about 0.9 inches. Atomic timekeeping ensures the watch displays accurate time and helps you keep your day in order. It receives a time signal from one of several international locations. An indicator allows you to check signal reception. This Citizen Eco-Drive watch for men also runs on light power. Its solar cell recharges automatically when direct sunlight or fluorescent light shines on the watch's dial. Although the solar cell is hidden beneath the round dial, the design allows light to enter the cell. It needs only five to six hours of light exposure per month to support the watch functions. An indicator reveals its power reserve. Use the watch's three chronographs like a stopwatch. They keep track of time up to 60 minutes. Two of the chronographs are in small dials within the watch's main dial. One of them displays a minute hand, and the other shows a 1/20th-second hand. The watch's one-second hand doubles as a chronographic second hand. All three chronographs operate with the press of a button. The watch's main dial has a third small dial that displays a 24-hour hand. This watch also shows the date and day of the week. Leap years and months under 31 days aren't a problem for its self-adjusting perpetual calendar. A Daylight Saving Time indicator may be switched on and off. Knowing the hour and date in different time zones throughout the planet is a snap with this watch. Easily find them for locations such as Paris, London, Sydney, Athens, Delhi, Bangkok, Tokyo, Beijing, and Rio de Janeiro. Pre-programmed settings also include U.S. cities such as Anchorage, Chicago, Denver, Honolulu, Los Angeles, and New York. The Blue Angels World Chronograph watch for men is 1.69 inches wide and about 0.5 inches thick. It weighs 0.63 ounces.
